<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wuxiaworld.com%2Fti-index%2Fti-vol-3-chapter-2-1%2F">Log in to Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div> 
</article> 
</li> 
<li class="comment byuser comment-author-mrvoid odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-502423">
<article id="comment-502423" class="comment-body">
<footer class="comment-meta">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img src="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Salt-copy5.png" width="50" height="45" alt="MrVoid" class="avatar avatar-50 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-50 alignnone photo"/><span class="fn"><b>MrVoid</b> <br/><a href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/ti-index/ti-vol-3-chapter-2-1/#comment-502423"><time datetime="2016-11-16T10:36:37+00:00"> November 16, 2016 at 10:36 am</time></a></span></div> </footer> 
<div class="comment-content">
<p>No, for f*cks sakes, please don&#8217;t let it have anything to do with Xuan. This is way too f*cking stupid, it&#8217;s not like this story doesn&#8217;t have enough tension going on for it with its basic premise, we don&#8217;t need more f*cking drama with stupid &#8220;who got a bigger d*ck&#8221; fights.<br/>
I agree that at least this level of danger brings some merit for Zhang to come back home, seeing as he accomplished nothing but get vaguely better with his Qi, and that&#8217;s about it. At least now something happens, that can only happen on Earth&#8230;But if it really has anything to do with Xuan, it&#8217;d happen for all of the wrong reasons.</p>
</div> 
